			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: BEP-RFC.  Verifying the author of a .torrent file (verified torrents).</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>This BEP is mostly inspired by the &quot;Verified Source&quot; feature of Torrentz.com, which I guess is one of the popular features of the site and assists greatly in choosing a torrent. This BEP just takes this feature to the core of the protocol.<br />Bringing this feature to core makes it also available to (including but not limited to) BitTorrent software (like Azureus/Vuze), especially when these software are being more and more independent from centralised servers (like searching*, getting metadata**, tracking***).<br /><br />[*] - Well, except searching for now.<br />[**] - Magnet URIs - <a href="http://bittorrent.org/beps/bep_0009.html" rel="nofollow">http://bittorrent.org/beps/bep_0009.html</a><br />[***] - DHT - <a href="http://bittorrent.org/beps/bep_0005.html" rel="nofollow">http://bittorrent.org/beps/bep_0005.html</a></p>
				</div>
				<div class="postsignature"><hr />-- Vikrant Chaudhary<br /><a href="http://vikrant.co.in/" rel="nofollow">http://vikrant.co.in/</a></div>
