				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: BEP-RFC.  Verifying the author of a .torrent file (verified torrents).</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<blockquote><div class="incqbox"><h4>Fredrik Neij wrote:</h4><p>However you could get around this by just signing the &quot;pieces&quot;+&quot;piece length&quot;, and have the &quot;author_key&quot; and signature in the info dict..</p></div></blockquote><p>Yes, the correct way to do it would be to rename &quot;encrypted_info_hash&quot; to &quot;encrypted_info&quot; (or &quot;signature&quot;) and make this field belong to &quot;info&quot; section.<br /><br />1. A hash is calculated of the &quot;info&quot; section including &quot;name&quot;, &quot;pieces&quot;, &quot;piece length&quot;,&nbsp; &quot;private&quot;, &quot;author_key&quot; and everything (except &quot;encrypted_info&quot;).<br />2. The above hash is encrypted using author's private key and is included in the &quot;info&quot; section as &quot;encrypted_info&quot;.<br />3. The &quot;info_hash&quot; can now be calculated.<br /><br />NOTE: We do a hash in Step#1 for only the purpose of encrypting it as encrypting plain text is not practical in PKC, and it may also generate errors like -&nbsp; &quot;RSAError: data too large for key size&quot;.</p>
					<p class="postedit"><em>Last edited by nasa42 (2010-03-10 23:39:05)</em></p>
				</div>
				<div class="postsignature"><hr />-- Vikrant Chaudhary<br /><a href="http://vikrant.co.in/" rel="nofollow">http://vikrant.co.in/</a></div>
