				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3> Re: BEP-RFC.  Verifying the author of a .torrent file (verified torrents).</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<blockquote><div class="incqbox"><h4>The 8472 - &quot;Azureus Developer&quot; wrote:</h4><p>The existence of several swarms (infohashes) describing the same content is already a problem today, adding more variables to the info dict only makes this problem worse.</p></div></blockquote><p>What would you say about key &quot;private&quot;, introduced by Azureus?<br /><br /></p><blockquote><div class="incqbox"><h4>The 8472 wrote:</h4><p>Instead of bulky RSA signature....</p></div></blockquote><p>RSA signatures aren't bulky. Just 128 bytes for a 1024-bit RSA key. Also using OpenPGP brings other benefits too, like &quot;web-of-trust&quot;, and gives choice of algorithm - RSA or DSA.<br /><br />We must at least keep the fingerprint inside the info dict. @mjfrancis has given a good example, which I'll try to repeat in short steps.<br /><br />(If fingerprint is outside of &quot;info dict&quot;) -<br /><br />1. There is a torrent ABCDEF created by Bob. Bob calculates the signature and does <em>attach(fingerprint,signature)</em>.<br />2. Eve calculates her own signature to the very torrent ABCDEF, does <em>attach(fingerprint,signature)</em> and claims that it belongs to her! <br /><br />* function <strong>attach(content)</strong> - content is either appended into .torrent metadata file outside &quot;info dict&quot; or added separately in magnet links.<br /><br />My original proposal was to keep fingerprint inside &quot;info dict&quot; and signature outside. But as @Fredrik Neij suggested to have both fingerprint and signature inside the &quot;info dict&quot;, which makes things simple (and it doesn't really add much overhead). Keeping both in the &quot;info dict&quot; has advantages like indexing sites and search engines can also verify the .torrent metadata file and display author information without going through any metadata exchange with other peers. (They'll have to query a keyserver for every new unique fingerprint, though).<br /><br />Another possible solutions is to keep fingerprint in the &quot;info dict&quot; and -<br />1. for .torrent metadata files - Keep signature outside the &quot;info dict&quot; but make it mandatory if fingerprint is present in the &quot;info dict&quot;.<br />2. for magnet links - add a parameter &quot;signature&quot; in the link.<br /><br />However this solution isn't reliable, as Eve can change the signature in .torrent metadata file or pass a magnet link without parameter &quot;signture&quot; which adds an overhead of getting the right signature somehow.<br /><br /><strong>UPDATE</strong> 23-March-2010 - Corrected 64 bytes for 1024-bit to 128 bytes.</p>
					<p class="postedit"><em>Last edited by nasa42 (2010-03-22 21:31:34)</em></p>
				</div>
